# VRT.Resume agent rules

**Canonical doc:** `AGENTS.md` at repo root. Read it before making changes.

## Non-negotiables

- Solution file: `VRT.Resume.sln` (repo has `.sln` + `.slnx`)
- Target: `net10.0`; package versions in `Directory.Packages.props` only
- CQRS via MediatR; handlers nested inside command/query types
- Errors via `Result` + `Errors.resx`; validation via FluentValidation pipeline
- No repository layer; `AppDbContext` used directly in handlers
- No EF migrations (`EnsureCreated` + seed on startup)
- Global MVC auth — mark public actions `[AllowAnonymous]`
- Tests in `VRT.Resume.Application.Tests.Unit/` are **integration tests** (LocalDB + Respawn 7)

## Git

- **Never `git push`** unless the user explicitly asks — they review locally first
- **After each completed PWA phase:** propose commit message (title + body) for user review

## Change discipline

- Minimal diffs; no drive-by refactors
- Reuse `UpsertHandlerBase`, `DeleteHandlerBase`, `HandlerBase`, `PersonEditControllerBase`
- New UI strings → `VRT.Resume.Resources` (.resx + .pl.resx)
- Verify: `dotnet build VRT.Resume.sln -c Release` && `dotnet test VRT.Resume.sln -c Release`

## Language

- Documentation, code comments, and commit messages: **English only**
- End-user UI: Polish + English via resource files

## VRT.Resume.Pwa

- **Blazor components:** markup-only `*.razor` + `partial class` in `*.razor.cs`; no `@code` blocks. Routed pages: `[Route(Routes.*)]` in code-behind (not `@page`); route constants in `Routes.cs`.
- **Feature-oriented layout** (vertical-slice style): `Features/{FeatureName}/` per feature; `Layout/` for shell; root for DI (`Program.cs`, `DependencyInjection*.cs`)
- PWA-specific code stays in `VRT.Resume.Pwa`; reuse `VRT.Resume.Application` via adapters — do not change Application for offline-only flows
- See `AGENTS.md` → **VRT.Resume.Pwa** for SqliteWasm, MudBlazor, EF 10.0.8 pin, and WASM pitfalls

